@zjffdu  yep would be great to have an option - if `ZEPPELIN_INTERPRETER_OUTPUT_LIMIT` is reached, for steaming data like KSQL, just remove first/oldest records in the output, so a paragraph can show live streaming data until it is explicitly stopped. again, this could be an option (e.g. `ZEPPELIN_INTERPRETER_STOP_ON_OUTPUT_LIMIT_REACHED`) like @conker84 has mentioned, perhaps made in a follow up change. 

